        "summary": {
          "diffs": [
            {
              "file": "bench-artifacts/cache-api.md",
              "patch": "Index: bench-artifacts/cache-api.md\n===================================================================\n--- bench-artifacts/cache-api.md\t\n+++ bench-artifacts/cache-api.md\t\n@@ -0,0 +1,68 @@\n+# Cache API\n+\n+The Cache API provides a simple key-value store for caching data.\n+\n+## createCache()\n+\n+Creates a new cache instance with basic key-value operations.\n+\n+```mjs\n+import { createCache } from './cache.mjs'\n+const cache = createCache()\n+```\n+\n+## Methods\n+\n+### get(key)\n+\n+Retrieves the value associated with the specified key from the cache. Returns the cached value if found, otherwise returns `undefined`.\n+\n+```mjs\n+cache.get('myKey') // returns the cached value\n+```\n+\n+### set(key, value)\n+\n+Stores the specified value under the given key in the cache. Returns the value after setting it.\n+\n+```mjs\n+cache.set('myKey', 'myValue') // returns 'myValue'\n+```\n+\n+### delete(key)\n+\n+Removes the cached entry for the specified key. Returns `true` if the key existed and was deleted, or `false` if the key was not found.\n+\n+```mjs\n+cache.delete('myKey') // returns true if deleted\n+```\n+\n+### clear()\n+\n+Removes all entries from the cache.\n+\n+```mjs\n+cache.clear() // clears all cached entries\n+```\n+\n+## Usage Example\n+\n+```mjs\n+const cache = createCache()\n+\n+// Store a value\n+const value = cache.set('user', userData)\n+\n+// Retrieve a value\n+const cachedValue = cache.get('user')\n+\n+// Remove a specific entry\n+cache.delete('user')\n+\n+// Clear all entries\n+cache.clear()\n+```\n+\n+---\n+\n+*Generated from [`cache.mjs`](./cache.mjs)*\n\\ No newline at end of file\n",
              "additions": 68,
              "deletions": 0,
              "status": "added"
            }
          ]
        },
